displayName: Golden City Dromos, Prince Faction Headquarters 2F

parameters: Clea (I have a bad feeling about this...)
Are we going down the stairs?
Clea (I have a bad feeling about this...)
Do you want to go down the stairs?

Clea: Long time no see. Back then, I really thought you were
a true adventurer.
Prince Rex: Hahaha, you don't have to be so formal.
Prince Rex: I'm glad everyone else seems to be doing well.

Thief Nora: L-Long time no see! That carriage ride back then
was so much fun!

Mage Relm: No need for introductions! From now on, please
recognize me as a candidate for Archmage!

Clea: I'll ask you straight to the point, Prince Rex. Do you
have any intention of aiming to become the king?
Clea: We were asked by Sophia-san to persuade Prince Rex.
Prince Rex: Sophia-san... um, she expects too much from me.

Prince Rex: I believe my father remarried Caron precisely
because I am not capable of bearing the burden of this great
empire.

Thief Nora: Um, what kind of relationship do you have with
Sophia-san...?

Prince Rex: They are not only the person who rescued me from
Caron's clutches, but also my comrade who went through the
escape journey together with me.

Prince Rex: Personally, I prefer the relationship of being
lovers the most.

Prince Rex: She's someone too precious for someone like me
who was saved at the risk of her life.

Mage Relm: Then why don't you grant our wishes? After all,
the first prince isn't even the legitimate successor,
right!?

Prince Rex: The guards were killed to capture me, and then
the guards were killed again to rescue me.

Prince Rex: If I were to declare myself as the successor, it
might lead to a civil war that would tear the empire apart.

Prince Rex: Did you see those people below? Most of my
supporters are ambitious fallen nobles aiming for a
reversal...

Prince Rex: The reason why this city of desires has its
headquarters here is because it's where the merchants who
profit from war are based.

Clea: You don't have the intention of becoming the king from
the bottom of your heart, do you?

Prince Rex: That's right... That's why I want Sophia-san to
give up.

Prince Rex: I don't think I have the determination or
strength to walk the path to the blood-soaked throne.
Prince Rex: That's why this should be the best option.
Prince Rex: I'm sorry for not meeting your expectations.

Prince Rex: Thank you for being my escort, Sophia. I'm
sorry, but I want you to gather everyone.

Priestess Sophia: Understood, I will inform everyone to come
immediately.

Prince Rex: I apologize for involving the Adventurer's Guild
in such a rough manner.
Clea: I will report this to the Guild Master.

Clea: I cannot agree with this kind of approach. It's
merciless to unilaterally slaughter someone who has no
intention to fight.

Clea: And also, I want Sophia-san to find a way that won't
make my dear friend sad.
Prince Rex: I will handle it. Your cooperation is essential.
Prince Rex: I killed my uncle, Pilia.

Prince Rex: Pilia opposed me, the legitimate heir to the
throne and supporter of Queen Caron's regime, which is why I
had to treat her as an enemy.

Prince Rex: This is a declaration of war against Queen
Caron!

Prince Rex: There will be a great amount of bloodshed from
now on, but at the end of that bloodshed, there will be a
throne, there will be justice!

Prince Rex: For the blood that has been shed, for the blood
that will be shed... I will definitely become the king... I
will take back the throne from Caron!

Priestess Sophia (Prince Rex... what on earth... even though
we're in the same place... I can't sense you)

Priestess Sophia (Will it reach you...? Like it did that
day... My voice... My heartbeat...)

Mansion Servant: It is my duty to protect the mansion until
the time comes.
Prince Rex: What I want to talk to you about is our future.
Priestess Sophia: Yes, I am prepared.

Prince Rex: You may have misunderstood something, but I have
no intention of letting go of Alicia or Sophia.

Prince Rex: I should have told you before, but I fell in
love at first sight, and I still feel the same way.

Prince Rex: You, who rescued me at that time, are the
greatest contributor when I become king.

Prince Rex: I won't let anyone complain or take orders from
anyone. I will decide who my partner is.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Looking back now, the
days when I escaped from pursuers with Prince Rex were the
most free and shining moments of my life.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: I was freed from the days
as a torturer and was able to spend time with the wonderful
person that is Prince Rex.

Young Rex: I was the same. It was when I had the heaviest
responsibility as a prince that my heart was the most
stable.

Young Rex: In front of me is a dignified yet adorable
woman... It was certainly a free and wonderful time for me
too.
Young Rex: How should I express something like that...

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Those were probably our
youth... The days of youth that came too late for us.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: And within our youth, we
fell in love.
Young Rex: That's right, that's why, I...

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: It was a love that burned
like fire, and yet, it wasn't love.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: We were too young for
love to grow in such a short time that it burns out.

Priestess Sophia: Now, I have changed from 'I' to 'you', and
you have changed from 'me' to 'I'...

Priestess Sophia: You have changed from a young man to a
prince, and I have changed from a torturer to a priestess...

Priestess Sophia: And so, the days of your youth as a prince
come to an end, and we have our own missions for each other.

Prince Rex: The innocent time has come to an end... That's
what I want to say.

Priestess Sophia: I will never forget the sun, the warmth,
and you, the young man from that day.

Priestess Sophia: I love you, Prince Rex, so please remember
me and us... and...

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Please forget about it
someday...

Prince Rex: It was the comrades who changed you, both
lovable and wonderful friends...

Prince Rex: I am just a persistent man. When I become king,
I want to hear your answer again.
